---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="Contribute"
  description="How to extend this Russia-focused fork of taiwan-md with better articles, references, datasets, and agent-ready integrations."
>
  <main class="page">
    <section class="wrap">
      <p class="eyebrow">Contribute</p>
      <h1>How to improve the fork</h1>
      <p>
        This repo is easiest to extend if contributions stay narrow and well-sourced. Add one article, one resource list,
        one chart, or one agent integration at a time. Keep the output readable for humans and legible for downstream LLMs.
      </p>
      <p>
        Treat this as a working fork of <a href="https://github.com/frank890417/taiwan-md" target="_blank" rel="noopener">`taiwan-md`</a>:
        preserve the strong upstream structure, but make changes explicit whenever Russia needs different framing, sources, or navigation.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="wrap cards">
      <article class="card">
        <h2>Writing</h2>
        <p>Add category essays, biographies, place explainers, and institution pages.</p>
        <p>Prefer clear structure, primary sources, and grounded claims over generic summaries.</p>
      </article>
      <article class="card">
        <h2>Data</h2>
        <p>Replace inherited placeholders with Russia-specific datasets from official or well-documented sources.</p>
        <p>Examples: Rosstat, CBR, FNS, federal ministries, regional portals, and reputable international datasets.</p>
      </article>
      <article class="card">
        <h2>Agent Skills</h2>
        <p>Extend <a href="/SKILLS.md">SKILLS.md</a> into concrete adapters or MCP-style tools.</p>
        <p>Document auth, read actions, write actions, and approval requirements explicitly.</p>
      </article>
    </section>

    <section class="wrap">
      <h2>Contribution rules</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Do not scrape private or undocumented state endpoints.</li>
        <li>Mark partner-gated APIs as partner-gated.</li>
        <li>Preserve raw source links in articles and data notes.</li>
        <li>Use reversible, reviewable commits.</li>
      </ul>
    </section>
  </main>
</Layout>

<style>
  .page {
    padding: 4rem 1.5rem;
  }

  .wrap {
    max-width: 900px;
    margin: 0 auto 2.5rem;
  }

  .cards {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(240px, 1fr));
    gap: 1.25rem;
  }

  .card {
    border: 1px solid #e2e8f0;
    border-radius: 20px;
    padding: 1.25rem;
    background: #fff;
  }

  .eyebrow {
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.14em;
    font-size: 0.78rem;
    color: #64748b;
  }

  p, li {
    line-height: 1.8;
    color: #334155;
  }
</style>
